od.name: Outlier Detection
od.des:
An outlier represents the data points which are not in the normal range as specified by 
        threshold values. Any datapoint outside the threshold values will be highlighted as outlier / anomalies. 
        We have given an overall scatter plot for the entire production dataset after reducing the data’s
        dimensionality if required. Apart from this, we have also given two plots for each feature. 
        One of them is a Probability Density Plot and the other one is a Box Plot. These plots represent 
        outliers with respect to the reference and production data.

dd.name: Drift Detection
dd.des:
Data drift identifies potential changes in the data inputs that may cause performance
        degradation of the model. This drift is detected by measuring and comparing probability distributions 
        of reference and production data using multiple, best in class, statistical methods. We have provided 
        a bar plot with p-values highlighting the drift in production data. Apart from this, for every 
        feature we have provided three graphs. They are, a Probability Density Plot, a Cumulative Distribution 
        Function plot and a Mean Bar Plot.

cd.name: production metric drift
cd.des:
Concept drift indicates the changes in model performance with respect to various metrics like
      Accuracy, AUC-ROC, F1 score etc. The Bar Plot given given represents percentage concept drift with 
      respect to these metrics.

ae.name: AE
ae.des:
Adversarial detection indicates the percentage of data points which are adversarial in nature 
      when compared to all data points in reference and production data. We have deployed multiple best in 
      class techniques to identify and detect data points which are perturbated. We are representing 
      adversarial perturbation in reference and production data through a Paired Bar Plot.

di.name: Data Integrity
di.des:
Data integrity indicates the total percentage of NaN(null) and OOR(Out of range)

        values in the production data as a bar plot. Apart from this, for every feature, we have provided

        the graphs which indicate the feature importance, Nan(null) and OOR(Out of range) percenatge

        of each feature.

Monitoring.name: Monitoring Alert
Monitoring.des:
Monitoring alerts indicate the percentage of outliers, drifted features, 

      adversarial samples, NaN(null) values and OOR(out of range) values in the production 

      data that go beyond the predetermined threshold value and is highlighted through a 

      different color. If the metric percentage is less than 2% then it is considered as a 

      normal alert (blue), if it is between 2% to 5% then it will appear as medium alert (yellow) 

      and if the metric percentage is beyond 5% then it will appear as a high alert (red). 

      The pie chart indicates the total number of normal, medium and high alerts. All the dropdown 

      buttons contain the information of the particular module such as alerts from the outlier 

      detection module, the drift detection module and more. Finally, the logs button contains 

      critical/Error log information if any.

bias_alert.name: Bias alert
bias_alert.des:
The bias alert bar chart only display metrics that have changed in production. 

        The y-axis indicates the percentage of change that occurred in these metrics. The pie chart 

        indicates the number of Normal, Medium and high alerts. The alert message button contains the 

        information of the changed metrics along with their percentage value.
